                        <p>
                            Since the end of World War II the United States has had a military presence in Japan. To prevent the defeated
                            Japanese Empire from rebuilding its military strength after the war, the  U.S. initially acted as an occupying
                            force. In the following decades, however, relations between the two countries improved and the two countries have
                            signed agreements in which the United States has agreed to come to the aid of Japan if Japan were to be attacked
                            by another nation.
                        </p>

                        <p class="block-quote">
                            <span id="openQuote">“</span>There are over 10,000 military personnel<br/>
